WEBVTT

01:06.167 --> 01:08.337
Hold your end up higher.

01:08.369 --> 01:10.699
- You're not holding it.
- I am too.

01:10.738 --> 01:13.638
- You are not.
- Don't worry about me.

01:13.674 --> 01:15.484
Mmm.

01:16.677 --> 01:20.507
- Isn't that suit charcoal?
- No.

01:20.548 --> 01:24.148
Looks charcoal gray to me.
Some gray polyester blend.

01:24.185 --> 01:25.585
You'd think you could

01:25.619 --> 01:27.619
find a black suit for
your own father's funeral.

01:27.655 --> 01:30.485
- It's black.
- No. I'm sure it's gray.

01:30.524 --> 01:32.364
- It's black. Black.
- Gray. Gray!

01:32.393 --> 01:33.863
- Black!
- Fine, it's black.

01:35.529 --> 01:37.429
It's the grayest black
I've ever seen.

01:37.465 --> 01:40.425
- Doesn't matter
what color it is!
- Oww!

01:44.538 --> 01:46.268
I'm sorry, Pop.
I'm sorry!

01:49.443 --> 01:52.213
[ thunks, splashes ]

01:59.520 --> 02:01.490
Quick!
Get him out of there!

02:01.522 --> 02:03.762
He's halfway to
the harbor by now, bub.

02:03.791 --> 02:05.791
Ah, well.

04:10.484 --> 04:14.694
[ man ] "I leave you
not just a model factory,

04:14.722 --> 04:18.791
but something
infinitely more valuable.

04:18.826 --> 04:23.956
The future of string...
itself."

04:23.997 --> 04:27.837
- [ explosion ]
- [ indistinct shouting ]

04:33.874 --> 04:37.044
"And thus it is
my dying wish

04:37.077 --> 04:41.347
that my two sons run
Smuntz String together."

04:41.382 --> 04:44.722
Great. Let's stick a
"For Sale" sign on the lawn
and see what we can get.

04:44.752 --> 04:46.952
Ernie, we're not
supposed to sell it.

04:46.987 --> 04:48.787
We're supposed to
run it together.

04:48.822 --> 04:51.732
Either way, this
Godforsaken museum piece

04:51.759 --> 04:53.959
is not worth a dime,
now is it, Lars?

04:53.994 --> 04:56.604
Some things are more
important than money, Ernie.

04:56.630 --> 05:00.470
Notice it's always
the financially challenged
who say that?

05:00.501 --> 05:03.501
Uh, please, please.

05:03.537 --> 05:06.937
"I also bequeath to you
my personal effects,

05:06.974 --> 05:11.314
including my ceramic egg...

05:14.081 --> 05:17.521
...half box of Cuban cigars...

05:17.551 --> 05:20.091
Oh! Yes, yes, yes, yes.

05:20.120 --> 05:25.460
- My collection of spoons."
- [ clattering ]

05:25.493 --> 05:29.363
[ Ernie ] My goodness, what
a treasure. What a legacy.

05:29.397 --> 05:32.397
Spoons! Spoons!

05:32.433 --> 05:34.473
So many spoons,
so little time.

05:34.502 --> 05:38.772
Oh! And, of course,
something no household
should be without.

05:38.806 --> 05:41.136
The ceramic egg!
Ooh-hoo-hoo.

05:41.174 --> 05:44.654
Can I have the egg?
Can I? Huh? Huh? No.

05:44.678 --> 05:47.818
- I want you to have it.
- Fine, I'll take it!

05:47.848 --> 05:51.418
If you find any real estate
on that desk, let me know.

05:51.452 --> 05:54.392
It seems there is also a house.

05:54.422 --> 05:56.922
- [ together ] A house?
- Yes, 5120 Nortondale.

05:56.957 --> 06:02.597
[ chuckles ] Your father
acquired it many years ago
as payment of a debt.

06:02.630 --> 06:06.700
He never lived there,
but it's interesting.

06:06.734 --> 06:09.004
It seems the previous owner

06:09.036 --> 06:11.736
was found locked
in a trunk in the attic.

06:11.772 --> 06:13.912
Wait a minute.
Is it worth anything?

06:13.941 --> 06:18.081
He was able to borrow $50,000
against it to pay his workers.

06:18.111 --> 06:20.481
Really? So what
is its value today?

06:20.514 --> 06:23.624
$50,000.

06:23.651 --> 06:28.191
Great. A worthless house and
a broken-down string factory.

06:28.221 --> 06:31.761
Oh, well. At least the day
wasn't a total loss.

06:31.792 --> 06:34.392
Thanks for the stogies, Pop.

06:35.896 --> 06:39.666
Wait. You can't go. We have
to go through all these papers.

06:43.236 --> 06:48.476
You'll have to excuse me.
I've got a date with the mayor.

06:48.509 --> 06:51.949
- [ thunderclap ]
- [ reporters chattering ]

06:53.581 --> 06:57.181
Mr. Mayor! Mr. Mayor,
over here! Mr. Mayor!

06:57.217 --> 06:59.087
Do you think your recent
triple heart bypass

06:59.119 --> 07:01.019
will affect your
campaign strategy?

07:01.054 --> 07:02.994
Now, Leslie,
I'm just here to eat.

07:04.792 --> 07:09.902
Ah, Monsieur  Maire,
Madame Maire,
welcome to Chez Ernie.

07:09.930 --> 07:13.900
[ French accent ]
Ah, what an honor it is to
have you in my humble bistro.

07:13.934 --> 07:16.774
Suivez-moi.
Oh, you brought the little ones.

07:16.804 --> 07:21.114
The little bicycle thieves.
Bonjour! Our very best table.

07:21.141 --> 07:23.911
- Have you lost a little weight?
- Oh, I...

07:23.944 --> 07:26.084
I think so!
I think you may be buff!

07:26.113 --> 07:29.183
[ laughs ] Je suis enchantÃ©
